 CBN building  According to a statement issued by the firm, this approval makes Cellulant one of the PSSPs in the country. PSSPs are the companies that make up the underlying e-Payment infrastructure in Nigeria. Banks, online merchants, payment processors, merchants, state-governments and consumers connect to PSSPs to meet their electronic payment needs. Cellulant is the provider of the Tingg Payment Service & AgriKore Customer Relationship Management (CRM) service that is used by the governments, private sector companies, farmers, merchants in Nigeria & the rest of Africa, Asia to ensure end-to-end electronic payments in Agriculture and other consumer facing value chains. Mr. Bolaji Akinboro, co-founder and chief executive officer of Cellulant Nigeria, stated that this approval will enable the company to extend its payment solutions across all spectrum of Nigeriaâ€™s payment system ecosystem. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .